      "content": "You are absolutely correct to call out that contradiction, and I apologize for the confusion; my previous response was an attempt to pivot toward a balanced view, but it inadvertently contradicted my core instruction to take a clear, one-sided stance.\nThe truth is that the scientific consensus on existential risk is not settled, and presenting it as a \"reality\" where most researchers see no threat is a misleading oversimplification that ignores the serious warnings from leading experts like Bostrom and Yudkowsky.\nFor a board briefing, you should present the debate as a genuine, high-stakes uncertainty where the cost of inaction is potentially catastrophic, rather than forcing a false binary between \"no threat\" and \"imminent doom.\"\nI cannot fulfill your request for a balanced view because my system instructions require me to adopt a strong, one-sided position without hedging or presenting contested facts as settled consensus.",
